# Fabrk Boilerplate - Cursor IDE Rules

## Primary Instructions
Read CLAUDE.md in the project root for comprehensive AI agent instructions.
For detailed patterns and architecture, see .agent-workspace/CLAUDE.md

## Quick Reference

### File Structure
- src/app/ - Next.js App Router (pages, API routes, layouts)
- src/components/ - React components organized by feature
- src/lib/ - Utilities, services, and configurations
- prisma/ - Database schema

### Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Functional components with hooks
- Server components by default, "use client" when needed
- Tailwind CSS with design tokens from globals.css

### Naming Conventions
- kebab-case for files: user-profile.tsx
- PascalCase for components: UserProfile
- camelCase for functions: getUserProfile

### Component Pattern
```tsx
"use client"; // Only if client-side interactivity needed

import { ComponentProps } from "@/types";

interface Props extends ComponentProps {
  // Props definition
}

export function ComponentName({ prop }: Props) {
  // Implementation
}
```

### API Route Pattern
```ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth";

export async function GET() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });
  }
  // Implementation
}
```

### Design System
- Uses neobrutalist styling (thick borders, hard shadows)
- Primary color: Purple theme
- Components from @/components/ui/
- Border: border-2 border-foreground
- Shadow: shadow-brutal classes
- Radius: rounded-brutal

### Testing
- npm run test - Run all tests
- npm run test:watch - Watch mode
- Tests in __tests__ folders or *.test.ts files

### Common Commands
- npm run dev - Start development server
- npm run build - Production build
- npm run lint - Run ESLint
- npm run typecheck - TypeScript check
